g.text: The use of light grey and drop shadow on the amenities help users identifiy which icons they haven’t yet selected.
The removal of the drop shadow and change of color to purple in addition to the appearance of the selected icon above indicates to users that their selection has been registered.
The workspace capacity filter utalizes uses a scrollable design most users would find familiar. The design defines the minimum and maximum values a user can enter.
The previously grey and hollow “Apply Filter” button changes form once options are applied, indiciating to users that the filters have been registered and are ready to be applied.
